#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

int main() {
    int n;
    cin >> n;

    for (int i = n; i >= 1; i--) {
        cout << i << " ";
    }

    return 0;
}
```
This code reads an integer `n` from the standard input, uses a `for` loop to iterate from `n` to 1 in reverse order, and prints each number followed by a space. The loop condition `i >= 1` ensures that the loop continues until `i` is 1, at which point it exits. The `return 0` statement is used to indicate the end of the program.
